- Don't summarize from message metadata alone (filename + poster name). The dollar amount is in the photo.
- Don't say "the channel was quiet this week" if the strict 7-day window is empty but there are forms from last week. Fall back to the most recent active week and label the date range.
- Don't try to download the Slack file via curl/web_fetch — the URLs require auth. Use Chrome MCP and the channel-archives URL.
- Don't schedule a placeholder and try to update it. Scheduled Slack messages cannot be edited via API. Either finish the work first, or send live with slack_send_message if you're past 9 AM.
- Don't blindly attribute by poster if the receipt header on the form clearly shows a different store. Receipt wins.
- **Don't end your turn with text after a Skill load or system reminder. Fire the next tool call.** This is the failure that caused the 2026-05-04 miss.
